#* {{zh-x|何謂 四靈？麟-鳳-龜-龍，謂 之 四靈。故 龍 以為{wéi} 畜，故 魚-鮪 不-淰{shěn}；鳳 以為{wéi} 畜，故 鳥 不-獝{yù}；麟 以為{wéi} 畜，故 獸 不-狘{xuè}；龜 以為{wéi} 畜，故 人情 不失。|What were the {{w|Four Holy Beasts|four numinous creatures}}? They were the lin, the feng, the tortoise, and the dragon. When the dragon becomes a domestic animal, (all other) fishes and the {{w|Chinese paddlefish|paddlefish}} '''do not dive underwater scared''' (from men). When the feng becomes so, the birds do not fly from them in terror. When the Qi-lin does so, the beasts do not scamper away. When the tortoise does so, the feelings of men take no erroneous course.|ref=Liji-L}}

